  %li.t-col.w-1-3.m-1-1
    .t-block.box-4
      .t-content
        %p Our approach includes understanding client and user requirements, information architecture, design principles, usability testing, and how these factors come together in the code that you write.
  %li.t-col.w-1-3.m-1-1
    .t-block.box-5
      .t-content
        %p Everything you implement will be on the Rails platform, from basic markup to advanced user agent detection for mobile device rendering. You will also learn how to deploy Ruby on Rails websites to top tier hosting providers like Heroku and Amazon AWS.
      .t-middle
        =# embedded_svg 'icons/svg/dev-2/ruby-original-wordmark.svg'
        = embedded_svg 'icons/svg/dev-2/rails-plain-wordmark.svg'
        = embedded_svg 'icons/svg/dev-2/heroku-plain-wordmark.svg'
        = embedded_svg 'icons/svg/dev-2/amazonwebservices-original.svg'
      .t-bottom
        %h4 Ruby, Rails, Heroku, Amazon AWS
  %li.t-col.w-1-3.m-1-1
    .t-block.box-6
      .t-content
        %p Along this process you will follow Best practices and standards for writing code, and you will learn how to research and solve problems, pair program, work in teams and contribute to larger projects, and ptimize and improve performance for the sites that you build.
      .t-bottom
        %h4 You will become a well-rounded full stack developer ready to join and contribute to any team.

